doc.ContractDescription: FSC: 8340 NAME: BOOTWALL,COMMAND

ALL FUTURE MAJOR X-RAY OBSERVATORIES WOULD BENEFIT FROM AN IMPROVEMENT IN THE ANGULAR RESOLUTION AND/OR COLLECTION AREA OF THE INSTRUMENT. THIS PROJECT WILL DEVELOP ZNO TRANSISTORS FOR INTERPOSER ELECTRONICS ON THIN FILM PIEZOELECTRIC ACTUATORS TO ADVANCE THIS GOAL. THESE ACTUATORS, DEPOSITED ON THE BACK OF GRAZING INCIDENCE MIRROR SEGMENTS, ARE THE CRITICAL STEP IN PRODUCING ADJUSTABLE XRAY OPTICS. THE INCORPORATION OF ELECTRONICS DIRECTLY ON THE THIN FILM PIEZOELECTRIC MATERIAL (PZT) WILL ENABLE SIMPLIFIED CONTROL OF INDIVIDUAL PIEZO CELLS AND INCREASE SYSTEM FAULT TOLERANCE. THUS, THIS DEVELOPMENT OFFERS A SIGNIFICANT REDUCTION TO THE ADJUSTABLE OPTICS MIRROR SYSTEM COMPLEXITY AND IMPROVEMENTS IN PERFORMANCE, GREATLY ENHANCING THE FEASIBILITY OF ADJUSTABLE X-RAY OPTICS. WE PROPOSE A SCALABLE ADJUSTABLE OPTICS SOLUTION FOR FUTURE HIGH RESOLUTION, LARGE COLLECTING AREA X-RAY TELESCOPES, IN WHICH THIN PZT FILMS WITH A LARGE NUMBER OF INDEPENDENTLY ADDRESSABLE ELECTRODES ARE DEPOSITED ON THE BACKS OF MIRROR ELEMENTS. APPLYING LOW VOLTAGE TO THE INDIVIDUAL PZT CELLS INTRODUCES LOCALIZED DEFORMATIONS IN THE MIRROR FIGURE, AND CAN BE USED TO CORRECT MIRROR FABRICATION, MOUNTING, THERMAL AND GRAVITY RELEASE ERRORS. THIS TECHNIQUE ENABLES THE USE OF THIN, LIGHT-WEIGHT OPTICAL ELEMENTS TO ACHIEVE SUBARCSEC ANGULAR RESOLUTION.
